  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the sous\u2011vide bath to 150\u202f\u00b0F (65\u202f\u00b0C).",
    "Season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, ras el hanout, and minced garlic.",
    "Place the seasoned chicken in a vacuum\u2011seal bag along with olive oil, maple syrup, chicken broth, and butter cubes.",
    "Seal the bag using a vacuum sealer or the displacement method.",
    "Cook the bagged chicken sous\u2011vide for 90\u2013120 minutes, until the internal temperature reaches 150\u202f\u00b0F (65\u202f\u00b0C).",
    "Remove the chicken from the bag and pat dry with paper towels.",
    "Heat a skillet over medium\u2011high heat; sear the chicken for 1\u20132 minutes per side, adding thyme sprigs during the last minute.",
    "Remove from heat, slice, and serve garnished with lemon zest."
  ],
